  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the Prevention of Risks of Deterioration of Social Cohesion and Peace in the Context of the Response to COVID-19 at Points of Entry and in Places of Detention in Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a response to support Burkina Faso in the fight against the COVID 19 pandemic will be based on capacity building of health management of entry points in order to prevent the deterioration of the social climate between populations and front-line actors and the establishment of a system to ensure the continuity of criminal justice and more efficient management in places of detention guaranteeing respect for the rights and freedoms of litigants during the pandemic period. Following its updated strategic plan for preparedness and response to COVID&apos;19, the project will support the Government in the implementation of its response to COVID&apos;19 in various places. As such, entry points in Burkina Faso, criminal courts and places of detention will be the target of the project. It will be implemented in collaboration with all institutions and actors of the justice field.</narrative>
  </description>
